title: Chris Christie cheers on the Mets at Citi Field (PHOTOS)
text:
NEW YORK â€” He's back.
A night after watching the Mets drub the Dodgers in Game 3 of the National League Division Series , Gov. Chris Christie reappeared at Citi Field to watch Game 4 Tuesday.
Seated in a private suite, Christie, dressed in a white button-up shirt and glasses, cheered the Mets, who were trying to close out the series and advance to the NL Championship Series against the Cubs.
